# 詞: 睇怕

1. 睇怕今晝間嘅颱風會影響出行，最好早啲出門啊。 (I'm afraid today's typhoon will affect travel; better leave early.)  
2. 佢遲咗半個鐘還未到，睇怕今日嘅項目討論會要推遲啦。 (He's half an hour late; I'm afraid today's project meeting will be postponed.)  
3. 呢本數學練習難到噉，睇怕班裡面十個有八個都做唔掂。 (This math workbook is so hard; I'm afraid eight out of ten students in the class can't finish it.)  
4. 電腦突然當機，睇怕我啱先存嘅文件係唔見咗咯。 (The computer crashed suddenly; I'm afraid the file I just saved is gone.)  
5. 天氣預報話有暴雨，睇怕今晚嘅夜跑計劃要泡湯囉。 (The weather forecast says there'll be a downpour; I'm afraid tonight's night run plan is ruined.)  
6. 阿爺食咗生冷嘢又話肚痛，睇怕要趕緊送佢去醫院先得。 (Grandpa ate cold food and says his stomach hurts; I'm afraid we need to send him to the hospital right away.)  
7. 商場門口停滿咗車，睇怕我哋要行遠啲先搵到停車位。 (The mall entrance is full of cars; I'm afraid we have to walk further to find a parking spot.)  
8. 佢發咗條訊息話“可能唔來”，睇怕係對我哋嘅聚會唔夠上心啊。 (He sent a message saying "maybe not coming"; I'm afraid he doesn't care much about our gathering.)  
9. 對手隊長受傷缺陣，睇怕我哋今場比賽贏面大咗好多。 (The opponent's captain is injured and absent; I'm afraid our chances of winning this game have increased a lot.)  
10. 鍋裡面嘅湯滾到溢出來，睇怕係火太大未調好火候囉。 (The soup in the pot is boiling over; I'm afraid the heat was too high and not adjusted properly.)  
